r alll humankind in every nation.', 2878, 0), (69835, 'Adventure begins when something goes wrong', 5149, 0), (69836, 'What is necessary is what is needed.', 2878, 0), (69837, 'If we dare the difficult, we shall find the depth of being.', 2878, 0), (69838, 'One and all they are driven by the twin engines of ignorance and willful barbarism. You nod, you also are familiar with these two powerful components of our national character, ignorance and willful barbarianism. Yes, everywhere you turn, and even among the most gifted of us, the most extensively educated, these two brute forces of motivation will eventually emerge. The essential information is always missing; sensitivity is a mere veil to self-concern. We are all secret encouragers of ignorance, at heart we are all willful barbarians.', 14946, 0), (69839, 'If we have reverence for God, we will have respect for one another.', 2878, 0), (69840, 'If you pray, you purify your heart.', 2878, 0), (69841, 'If you respect yourself, you will respect others.', 2878, 0), (69842, 'I was never really about the money. Every business I''ve ever started has been more of a curiosity and a kind of "What if...', 14947, 0), (69843, 'The desires of the flesh leads to sin. But the delight of the spirit leads to life.', 2878, 0), (69844, 'The delight of the spirit leads to life.', 2878, 0), (69845, 'In times of trouble, turn to God.', 2878, 0), (69846, 'We are shaped by every endured situation.', 2878, 0), (69847, 'Conquer no man than yourself.', 2878, 0), (69848, 'There is something about yourself that you don''t know. Something that you will deny even exists until it''s too late to do anything about it. It''s the only reason you get up in the morning, the only reason you suffer the shitty boss, the blood, the sweat and the tears. This is because you want people to know how good, attractive, generous, funny, wild and clever you really are. "Fear or revere me, but please think I''m special." We share an addiction. We''re approval junkies. We''re all in it for the slap on the back and the gold watch. The "hip, hip, hoo-fucking-rah." Look at the clever boy with the badge, polishing his trophy. Shine on, you crazy diamond. Cos we''re just monkeys wrapped in suits, begging for the approval of others.', 14948, 0), (69849, 'If we fail to listen to music, we shall be miserable.', 2878, 0), (69850, 'New karma is being made all the time. When one acts with a positive motivation, goodness is furthered. When one acts out of negative motivation, negativity is furthered. "We can recondition ourselves to act with wisdom. The important thing to understand here is that you are not a victim. You are your own master. ''As you sow, so shall you reap.', 4789, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (69851, 'To just be--to be--amidst all doings, achievings, and becomings. This is the natural state of mind, or original, most fundamental state of being. This is unadulterated Buddha-nature. This is like finding our balance.', 4789, 0), (69852, 'It don''t matter where you''re at ''cause you ain''t there yet.', 14949, 0), (69853, 'Without a song, life is a sorrow.', 2878, 0), (69854, 'The moment is a miracle.', 2878, 0), (69855, 'Whatever a man needs is within himself.', 2878, 0), (69856, 'I might be a witness to those who didn''t confident in themselves, but I will not be like them.', 14950, 0), (69857, 'The hatred of those who hate me is like a boomerang to them', 14950, 0), (69858, 'Is it better to be useful than successful?', 2878, 0), (69859, 'Bitterness is captivity.', 2878, 0), (69860, 'Just imagine, life to be a dance with different kind of rhythms depending on what music is playing in the background. Sometimes we may dance alone and that’s OK, as some songs are simply meant to be danced like that. Practice! Don’t stop! It’s your dance! ', 7564, 0), (69861, 'The real fun of life is in laughing', 14951, 0), (69862, 'No one needs to give you permission to be great. You hold that authority.', 5766, 0), (69863, 'Don''t try to live forever - You can''t! But you can do things that will live forever.', 5635, 0), (69864, 'I fear death. I think I must learn to romanticize death so that I can cope with its brutal irreversible numbness...!', 5762, 0), (69865, 'A Woman who let out a Sigh Outside a Mansion, should Never ask her Husband Why He Works Late', 5167, 0), (69866, '​You can''t Believe in Yourself, till People Believe in You.', 5167, 0), (69867, 'There are an incalculable—even infinite—number of situations in which we can practice forgiveness. Expecting it to be a singular action—motivated by the sheer imperative to move on and forget—can be more damaging than the original feelings of anger. Accepting forgiveness as pluralistic and as an ongoing, individualized process opens us up to realize the role that our own needs play in conflict resolution.', 124, 0), (69868, 'Mirror mirror on the wall,Show me the one who can conquer it all', 5149, 0), (69869, 'I prefer to die fighting than living defeated', 12179, 0), (69870, 'Life is not a Race, but we still continue the Chase and try to be an Ace. It’s time to get out of this Maze and Truly Live with Grace.', 5635, 0), (69871, 'A simple "Hi" has potential to make you blush, if received from your crush ...', 14952, 0), (69872, 'Loving kindness is the practice of offering to oneself and others wishes to be happy, peaceful, healthy, strong', 124, 0), (69873, 'We begin to cultivate real love for ourselves when we treat ourselves with compassion.', 124, 0), (69874, 'A lack of real love for ourselves is one of the most constricting, painful conditions we can know.', 124, 0), (69875, 'As you start and end your day, say THANK YOU for every little things in your life. And you will come to realize how blessed you truly are.', 14952, 0), (69876, 'Indigence is one of those states, politicians less likely wish to manage.', 10412, 0), (69877, 'You see, at young age I had known how bitter taste like and it all started with a cup of brewed coffee.', 10412, 0), (69878, 'My get-up-and-go often leaves without me.', 9426, 0), (69879, 'Hurting someone will not impress them. Intelligence requires empathy to work. Water is wet. The sky is pink through these rose-tinted glasses.', 7578, 0), (69880, 'If you''re doing something you love, it doesn''t matter that it''s challenging. You can keep going for a long time as long as you''re motivated- just make sure you choose the right starting point. If you''re lucky, as happened with Stephen, Your inclination may even become a vocation.', 6340, 0), (69881, 'I am a deeply uncertain individual. I often find myself acting like a fool to make the people around me laugh. When they’re laughing, they’re not watching me quite as closely. I smile to put people at ease. But what if I opened my mouth one day, spoke my actual thoughts, and the people glared at my opinions? What if they thought me disgusting or frightening or ugly because of my words? Would you keep your lips shut for the rest of your life to not face that judgment? Just for the sake of someone else’s comfort? For these strangers, who I will never know? If I can’t speak then I’ll write. These strangers, whose opinions crush me, will be forced to listen. Because when they read my words those words will make a home within their heads. They may even end up using my own opinions against me. But at least I’ll be hidden behind the pages of a book.', 7578, 0), (69882, 'Money is important, no doubt it is. But is it everything? That''s the question we miss when we make our Choices in Life.', 5635, 0), (69883, 'Confidence is not what others think about you, it''s what you think about yourself', 14953, 0), (69884, 'Strange satisfaction of organizing pencil crayons and sharpening them (the way I used to enjoy sharpening wax crayons as a kid ', 7587, 0), (69885, 'Humans'' eyes cannot take in information when there is zero light reflecting back', 7509, 0), (69886, 'nothing motivated a person quite as much as the desire for vengeance.', 14954, 0), (69887, 'The journey to more self love is often a quiet and long road. One without cheerleaders or confetti. Just you and your strong inner conviction to do things differently. There are both triumphs and failures on this road. And when you truly turn a corner you will bask in quiet victory, finally feeling the power you once thought was elsewhere.', 4944, 0), (69888, 'Your body expresses yesterday in what it wants today. If you think: yesterday I was, tomorrow I shall be, you are thinking: I have died a little. Be what you are becoming, without clinging to what you might have been, what you might yet be. Never settle. Leave definitiveness to the undecided; we don''t need it.', 14955, 0), (69889, 'We don''t always get what we want but often something better happens and we become the person we always wanted to be.', 4944, 0), (69890, 'As events beyond my control unfold. I go within to find peace.', 4944, 0), (69891, 'There comes a time to speak your truth and the time is now', 4944, 0), (69892, 'I am now ready to let go of anyone or anything that prevents me from being me.', 4944, 0), (69893, 'Thank you to all the people who have triggered my issues. You have helped me clarify what they are, start the healing process and ultimately become a better person.', 4944, 0), (69894, 'Once you realize the magic of life is inside you', 14956, 0), (69895, 'Today I make time to release any burdens that I carry. One by one I release them into the atmosphere, until my body is in a complete state of calm', 4944, 0), (69896, 'If you truly want the universe to support you in becoming all you can be', 14957, 0), (69897, 'When you claim your amazing, limitless self you are simply owning the highest truth of who you are.', 4944, 0), (69898, 'To be a world changer', 14958, 0), (69899, 'People ask – how can I enjoy life when I have problems? You may have problems, but you can still enjoy life and be Happy.', 5635, 0), (69900, 'There is nothing lacking in you. You came into this life as an abundant being. You remain as such. Free your heart and mind from anything but this truth.', 4944, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (69901, 'Sometimes it''s about standing in your power.', 4944, 0), (69902, 'Many of us learned to repress our creativity. We were told it was secondary to more important skills. The good news is that many of us have untapped gifts just waiting to be expressed. You owe it to yourself to uncover and express your gifts', 4944, 0), (69903, 'It is not over, unless you stop trying.', 10427, 0), (69904, 'If you believe all those who are urging you to give up are wrong, prove them wrong!', 10427, 0), (69905, 'Once you “believe” that you can do it and do take the first step forward, stop doubting yourself.', 10427, 0), (69906, 'Competition in business is a blessing, for without it, we wouldn’t be motivated to improve.', 10427, 0), (69907, 'Whether you dream big or dream small, chances are your dream will come true if you believe in it and really work on it.', 10427, 0), (69908, 'When I was a boy of seven or eight I read a novel untitled "Abafi" — The Son of Aba — a Servian translation from the Hungarian of Josika, a writer of renown. The lessons it teaches are much like those of "Ben Hur," and in this respect it might be viewed as anticipatory of the work of Wallace. The possibilities of will-power and self-control appealed tremendously to my vivid imagination, and I began to discipline myself. Had I a sweet cake or a juicy apple which I was dying to eat I would give it to another boy and go through the tortures of Tantalus, pained but satisfied. Had I some difficult task before me which was exhausting I would attack it again and again until it was done. So I practiced day by day from morning till night. At first it called for a vigorous mental effort directed against disposition and desire, but as years went by the conflict lessened and finally my will and wish became identical.', 1908, 0), (69909, 'When someone influences you to think negatively, they take Charge of your Life and will lead you to Destruction.', 5635, 0), (69910, 'You must prune to bloom. If the dead weight is not pruned and removed, it compromises the quality, performance, and output of the vine. When you prune what’s not working in your life, you make the space and place for renewal to happen and for new growth to spring forth.', 11252, 0), (69911, 'Moments of reflection occur with calm deliberation and careful thought. Imagine the thoughts which would come to you if you would simply allow them. By giving intentional consideration to a situation, you will gain clarity which you may not have achieved otherwise.', 11252, 0), (69912, 'Life is a choice. We can be truly Happy or miserable ! Or in-between .... We decide.', 5635, 0), (69913, 'Perfecting your character isn’t a marathon, a race, or a competition. It can only be won in stride with daily motivation.', 12324, 0), (69914, 'I''LL LET YOU FREE IN MY NEVERLAND ', 14952, 0), (69915, 'as you know that prior to Search Enggine (google, yahoo, bing etc) our knowledge comes from books. and we often underestimate the cover of the book before reading it. where the universe and everything in it were all neatly recorded in the book .. but unfortunately, lately reduced book reader interest. and tonight I say that the inspiration of the book far more powerful than anything .. not even a lot of writers who took also into his imagination. yes, I started to read', 14952, 0), (69916, 'I WILL REJECT DEATH IF I KNOW HAND COME"but .....................We would not be able to resist the will of god.Whenever, wherever you are. may god is ready to take your life.and honestly death is only the secrets of god almighty one.', 14952, 0), (69917, 'Never underestimate the power of pain. Once it''s revealed, you would see the unexpected result coming up.', 14959, 0), (69918, 'Not all angels come from above. Some are beside you or around you even as we speak. Then why can''t we see them? Because we are too busy searching for them elsewhere. We won''t find them unless we stop looking for 